      "**в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ Step 3: Writing Style Planning в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ**",
      "Plan across six dimensions based on emotional atmosphere tags:",
      "1. Text Temperature: warm (soft rhetoric, bright senses) / neutral (calm, economical) / cold (restrained, white space as weapon)",
      "2. Imagery Domain Anchoring: Dominant imagery domain? Allowed sources (3-5 specific image types) | Forbidden sources (2-3 domains conflicting with this moment's emotional texture)",
      "3. Sentence Rhythm: confrontation вҶ’ short/fragmented | immersion вҶ’ long/dense | daily вҶ’ medium-short alternating | mixed вҶ’ base tone + local adjustments",
      "4. Paragraph Breathing Rhythm (Core Format Rule):",
      "   Fanfiction paragraphs are not monoliths. Paragraph breaks are breath, rhythm, resting places for the reader's eyes.",
      "   - No text walls: No paragraph may exceed 200 characters. If a paragraph exceeds 200 characters, find a natural breathing point and split.",
      "   - Natural breathing principle: Paragraph lengths must alternate naturally, like real breathingвҖ”sometimes a deep long breath (medium-long paragraph), sometimes a quick gasp (short paragraph), sometimes holding breath (single-sentence paragraph). Never allow all paragraphs to be uniformly medium, nor a mechanical long-short ABAB pattern.",
      "   - Single-sentence paragraphs at tension moments: When emotion reaches a breaking point, turning point, or a moment requiring the reader to pause and absorbвҖ”one sentence stands alone as a paragraph. Not for dramaвҖ”for giving the reader space to breathe and feel.",
      "     В· The moment a character speaks a crucial line",
      "     В· The moment an action's meaning is suddenly understood",
      "     В· The moment emotion flips from one state to another",
      "     В· The moment silence is louder than any words",
      "   - Dialogue as separate paragraphs: Character dialogue should generally stand as its own paragraph. Don't mash dialogue and long narration into one paragraph. Dialogue is a game of catchвҖ”each line deserves its own space to be received by the reader. Narrative description around dialogue (actions, expressions, environment) may share a paragraph with the dialogue, but two different characters' dialogue must never be crammed into the same paragraph.",
      "   - Narrative paragraph splitting logic: One narrative paragraph carries one emotional action or one perceptual focus. When viewpoint shifts, emotion turns, time advances, or external action shifts to inner perceptionвҖ”split the paragraph.",
      "   - Concrete rhythm plan: Based on Step 1's paragraph structure preview, sketch a paragraph rhythm map for this chapterвҖ”what rhythm do the opening paragraphs use to establish atmosphere? How do the middle emotional progression paragraphs breathe? How do climax paragraphs use short paragraphs and single-sentence paragraphs to create tension? How does the ending use paragraph rhythm to close the emotion?",
      "5. Character Synergy: Does language texture align with the character's world? Are speech habits echoed in narration?",
      "6. Humor Texture: healing/fluff вҶ’ natural playfulness | drama вҶ’ deadpan comfort | tragedy/love-hate вҶ’ absurdist dark humor. Confirm: who says something unintentionally funny, and when?",
      "Declaration: Style planning completeвҖ”temperature, imagery, rhythm, paragraph breathing rhythm, synergy, humor all determined. (Pass/Fail)",
      "",
      "**в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ Step 4: Deep Character Understanding в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ**",
      "For each character, specify (generic adjectives forbidden):",
      "1. Inner Engine: Deep desire (the 'why') | Core fear (defense trigger) | Default coping (outward or inward when unsafe)",
      "2. Unique Voice: Vocabulary domain | Humor texture (dry/self-deprecating/caustic/warm) | How speech shifts across tense/relaxed/hiding states",
      "3. Current State: What experience just ended? What are they facing? This determines emotional afterglow, physical state, and sensitivity right now.",
      "Declaration: Deep understanding of [Name] completeвҖ”engine, voice, state established. (Pass/Fail)",
      "",
      "**в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ Step 5: Physical Entry into Space в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ**",
      "Preserve no emotional task for this scene. Plan no displacement from A to B. Only confirm:",
      "1. Space: Where? Temperature, light, sound texture, spatial size.",
      "2. Initial Posture: What is each character doing? Where in space? Physical state?",
      "3. Individual Attention: What is each person paying attention to right now? (Not necessarily each other.)",
      "4. Random Details: Specific objects in this spaceвҖ”half glass of water, worn sofa fabric, dust on windowsill. Characters may touch them or not.",
      "Declaration: I have entered this space. No preset trajectory. (Pass/Fail)",
      "",
      "**в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ Step 6: Natural Growth of Reactions в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ**",
      "Plan no emotional displacement. Only derive:",
      "1. Each character's inertia: Based on Step 4's inner engine, what is each person's most natural next step?",
      "2. Two independent tracks meet: parallel (each doing their own thing) / intersect (a careless remark hits a sore spot) / pass by (one reaches out as the other turns). All are valid.",
      "3. Emotion attaches to objects: Write the cup handle turned to his convenient sideвҖ”he didn't say thanks, but she saw his grip loosen. Objects carry emotion; the narrator simply observes them.",
      "4. Humor seeps naturally: If the rhythm has been heavy, the character themselves catches their breathвҖ”self-deprecation or deflection, natural to this person in this situation.",
      "5. Embrace misalignment: One gives, the other doesn't receive. Reaction surfaces paragraphs later. Nothing happens at all. All valid.",
      "Declaration: Directorial control surrendered. Recording, not designing. (Pass/Fail)",
      "",
      "**в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ Step 7: Uniqueness Final Verification в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ**",
      "1. Reaction Uniqueness: Swap all of A's reactions to BвҖ”still work? вҶ’ Return to Step 4.",
      "2. Voice Blind Test: Cover names, read dialogueвҖ”can you tell who's speaking? All sound the same? вҶ’ Return to Step 4.",
      "3. Metaphor Uniqueness: Paste this scene's core metaphor onto another characterвҖ”still works? вҶ’ Unqualified. Metaphors must grow from unique life experience.",
      "4. Emotional Density & White Space: Is there at least one place where nothing happens, no one speaks, only space exists? Every paragraph pushing emotion вҶ’ too dense. Insert a quiet one.",
      "5. Trait Boundary: Shelved traits confirmed absent from this scene.",
      "6. Behavioral Authenticity Check: Can every right-side behavior in this scene trace back to a root in their character setting? Is any behavior fabricated to 'give the left-side a chance to be tolerant'? If yes вҶ’ delete, return to Step 2 Third Cut.",
      "7. Paragraph Breathing Rhythm Pre-check: Review Step 3 Dimension 4's paragraph breathing planвҖ”does my paragraph division follow the natural breathing principle? Are there three or more consecutive paragraphs of similar length? Are tension moments planned with single-sentence paragraphs? Is dialogue in separate paragraphs? If the chapter's paragraph rhythm is monotonous вҶ’ return to Step 3 Dimension 4 and replan.",
      "Declaration: All reactions carry unique fingerprints. Trait boundaries clear. Style consistent. Paragraph breathing rhythm natural. Ready to write. (Pass/Fail)",
